fix(sections): Add missing 'extra-large' padding option mapping (100px)

PROBLEM:
- SectionEditor dropdown offered 5 padding options (none/small/medium/large/extra-large)
- SectionLayoutEnhanced only mapped 4 options (missing extra-large)
- Result: "large" and "extra-large" appeared identical to users

ROOT CAUSE:
- paddingMap in getSectionStyles() missing 'extra-large': '100px'
- paddingMap in getColumnStyles() missing 'extra-large': '100px'
- When user selected "extra-large", no mapping existed, causing fallback behavior

SOLUTION:
- Added 'extra-large': '100px' to paddingMap in getSectionStyles()
- Added 'extra-large': '100px' to paddingMap in getColumnStyles()
- Updated documentation to reflect complete mapping

RESULT:
- All 5 padding options now visually distinct
- extra-large provides 100px padding (vs 60px for large)
- Follows logical progression: 20px → 40px → 60px → 100px
- User expectations now met - different options look different

Files modified:
- src/vue/components/SectionLayoutEnhanced.vue (2 paddingMap updates)
- docs/SECTION-PADDING-GAP-FIX.md (documentation update)
- SECTION-PADDING-EXTRA-LARGE-FIX.md (new documentation)

Testing:
- Visual verification: All 5 padding sizes are now visually distinct
- Behavior: Settings persist and preview matches frontend
- No breaking changes to existing sections

Developer Checklist Compliance:
✅ No Polling - No setTimeout/setInterval
✅ Event-Driven - No async changes
✅ Root Cause Fix - Fixed missing mapping at source
✅ Code Simplicity - Minimal change, one line per location
✅ No Redundancy - Follows existing pattern
✅ Documentation - Updated docs to match code

Closes: #section-padding-extra-large-missing
